HEADWORD: Traducianism
<hw>Tra*du"cian*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Theol.)</fld>
<def>The doctrine that human souls are produced by the act of
generation; -- opposed to <xex>creationism</xex>, and
<xex>infusionism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Traducible</ent>⟦br⟧
